All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AddScreeningSchedule
Boundary/View Class for Admin personnel to add, modify, delete a showSchedule
Admin
Entity Class representing an Admin account Sub Class of a person
AdminController
A class of CRUD operations on the admin.dat, settings.dat and holiday.dat file Calls RWController to read and write data into .dat file
Booking
Entity Class representing a Booking
Boundary
abstract class representing a Boundary For ALL boundary classes to override and extend
CRUDCustomerBooking
A class of CRUD operations on the Booking.dat file Calls RWController to read and write data into .dat file
CRUDMovies
A class of CRUD operations on the Movies.dat & Reviews.dat file Calls RWController to read and write data into .dat file
CRUDShowSchedule
A class of CRUD operations on the ShowSchedule.dat file Calls RWController to read and write data into .dat file
CRUDTheatre
A class of CRUD operations on the Theatre.dat file Calls RWController to read and write data into .dat file
Customer
Entity Class representing a Customer A subclass inheriting from Person super class
CustomerController
A class of CRUD operations on the Customer.dat file Calls RWController to read and write data into .dat file
DisplayAdminRegiserBoundary
Boundary/View Class representing registration of accounts for the Admin
DisplayBookingConfirmation
Boundary/View Class to display booking confirmation after the movieGoer chooses Seats
DisplayBookingHistoryBoundary
Boundary/View Class to display the past booking history of the moviegoer if logged in as member, automatically provide details of past bookings else as a guest, enter email used to booked the ticket to check past bookings
DisplayMovieDetailsBoundary
Boundary/View Class to display the details of each movie after selecting one movie from the listing of the movies
DisplayMovieGoerRegisterBoundary
Boundary/View Class for moviegoers to register an account in order to log in as a member
DisplayMovieListBoundary
Boundary/View Class to list all the movies/ top 5 movies to the users, then afterwards users can proceed to check on the showschedules pertaining to the movie chosen
DisplayReviewBoundary
Boundary/View Class to display the review pertaining to a specific movie
DisplaySearchMovieBoundary
Boundary/View Class to search for a movie instead of listing all the movies
DisplayShowTimeBoundary
Boundary/View Class to display showScheduling based on a movie
DisplayShowtimeDetailMenu
Boundary/View Class representing a the Moviegoer to make a booking corresponding to a particular showtime
DisplayTop5MoviesBoundary
Boundary/View Class to display the Top 5 movies based on either rating, salesnumber or both (Only can be changed by system settings by Admin) or choose to book ticket as a guest
Holiday
Entity Class representing a Holiday For booking tickets, when the showschedule date coincides with a holiday prices would be affected
HolidayBoundary
Boundary/View Class representing an Admin to add/remove a Holiday
Initialiser
This interface is for the respective classes to override the initialise() method
MiscMethods
Represents the miscellaneous controller methods to be used across the entire application.
MoblimaMain
Boundary/View Class representing a the main menu that kickstarts the app
ModifyMovieDetails
Boundary/View Class for an admin to modify the details of a particular movie
ModifySystemSettingsBoundary
Boundary/View Class For the Admin to tweak the system settings, such as price, holidays and top five movie listings
ModifyTheatreBoundary
Boundary/View Class representing a the Moviegoer main after logging in as member or choose to book ticket as a guest
Movie
Entity Class representing a Movie A particular Movie Class contains all of the details about a movie, the enums of movieStatus and ageAdvisory, as well as take down and release Dates(for computation of End of Show, Preview, Coming Soon Status)
MovieEnums
An Class Containing the various enum Classes catering to the configuration of a particular movie
MovieEnums.AgeAdvisory
This enum class shows the AgeAdvisory category of a movie to be chosen.
MovieEnums.MovieStatus
This enum class shows the Status of the movie to be Chosen
MovieGoerMain
Boundary/View Class representing a the Moviegoer main after logging in as member or choose to book ticket as a guest
MovieGoerMainLogin
Boundary/View Class representing logging in as a moviegoer member
MovieGoerSelection
Boundary/View Class representing a Moviegoer page to either book tickets as guest, or log in as a member
MovieListingEditBoundary
Boundary/View Class enables the Admin to editing a list of movies, by appending, modifying and remove the movies from the list
Person
Entity Class representing a Person For MovieGoer and Admin Sub-classes
Review
Entity Class representing a Review the reviews must be tagged to a particular movie
RWController
Represents the main Controller Class for reading/writing the respective .dat files
Seat
Entity Class representing a Particular Seat in a ShowSchedule includes methods to print the layout of EACH seat, be it normal seats or couple seats
ShowSchedule
Entity Class representing a ShowSchedule A particular ShowSchedule contains all of the Seat Classes, and associates with Movie and Theatre Class to extract the movie and theatre details
StaffMain
Boundary/View Class representing an Admin's main portal after log in
SupportFunctions
Some support functions for the Boundary Classes
SystemSettings
Entity Class representing a SystemSetting by the Admin user
Theatre
Entity Class representing a Theatre A Theatre can be configured according to 3D, theatreclass, cineplex, location and code.
TheatreEnums
An Class Containing the various enum Classes catering to the settings of the theatre
TheatreEnums.CinemaLocation
This enum class shows the locations of the theatres to be chosen
TheatreEnums.Cineplex
This enum class shows the cineplex brand to be chosen
TheatreEnums.TheatreClass
This enum class shows the classes of the theatres to be chosen
